  Tokyo  Electric Power Co.
continues to struggle with the situation at a damaged nuclear
power plant, as several embassies in Tokyo advise foreign
nationals to consider leaving. Nomura Securities says the
Ministry of Finance may intervene in the foreign exchange
market today, with the yen hitting a post-World War II high
against the dollar.  WHAT TO WATCH
*Attempts continue to control the situation at the Fukushima
Dai-Ichi and Dai-Ni nuclear reactors
*Chief Cabinet Secretary Yukio Edano updates at 11 a.m.
*Hisahito Suzuki, chairman of the General Insurance
Association of Japan, gives regular press conference at 3 p.m.  ECONOMY
*Tertiary industry index for February were announced at 8:50
a.m.
*Bank of Japan minutes for its meetings on Feb. 14 and 15
were released at 8:50
*Oil consumption figures for January released at 1:30 p.m.
*Land value prices as of January 1 announced at 4:50 p.m.
 